  "response": "No, marks from pre-board exams are **not** added to calculate the CGPA (Cumulative Grade Point Average) for Class X.\n\n*   **Pre-boards are practice exams:** Pre-board exams are conducted by schools to give students a feel for the actual board exams and to assess their preparation. They are internal assessments and do not have any weightage in the final board results.\n\n*   **CBSE/ICSE Board Exams determine the CGPA:** The CGPA is calculated based solely on the marks obtained in the final Class X board examinations conducted by the respective education boards (e.g., CBSE, ICSE).\n\nTherefore, you don't need to worry about your pre-board scores affecting your final CGPA. They are primarily for your own self-assessment and to identify areas where you need to improve before the actual board exams.\n",
